+// Cloakfox: NON-self-destructing query for whether the per-container
+// "configured" flag is set for a given spoofer manager. Used by the
+// extension's core-bridge.ts to decide whether to add a signal to the
+// `handled` set on second+ navigations, where the corresponding
+// setXxx WebIDL method is no longer bound (Func-gated by the disabled
+// flag) and callCore() returns false. Without this query the JS
+// fallback runs on every nav after the first, defeating C++.
+//
+// `name` accepts: canvas, screen, webglVendor, webglRenderer, fontList,
+// fontSpacing, audio, speechVoices, navigatorUserAgent, navigatorPlatform,
+// navigatorOscpu, navigatorHardwareConcurrency.
+//
+// PRIVILEGE GATE: only the cloakfox-shield extension's content scripts
+// (which run with an ExpandedPrincipal containing the addon's principal)
+// can see this method on the window. Page scripts in MAIN world get an
+// undefined property — they can't even probe whether Cloakfox is
+// installed via this method. Every Cloakfox setter (setHttp2Profile,
+// setHttp3Profile, setCloakConfig, setCanvasSeed, setWebGLVendor,
+// setWebGLRenderer, setScreenDimensions, setScreenColorDepth,
+// setFontList, setFontSpacingSeed, setAudioFingerprintSeed,
+// setSpeechVoices, setNavigator*) is gated the same way.
+partial interface Window {
+  [Throws, Func="nsGlobalWindowInner::IsCloakfoxShieldCaller"]
+  boolean cloakfoxIsConfigured(DOMString name);
 };
 
